# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Config file for MacOS's libedit (aka editline).
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Explanation:
# MacOS doesn't ship with a full GNU readline implementation because of licensing issues. Instead,
# it provides its own, partially compatible line editing library, called libedit and frequently
# referred to as editline. Various programs use libedit, and various system libraries are linked
# against it, so some things that you might expect to honor ~/.inputrc won't. When using zsh, the
# line editor is ZLE, so a lot of this is hidden to zsh users, but it'll pop up in programs written
# to work with libedit. I especially want vi mode all the time, which normally comes from the
# "set editing-mode vi" line in ~/.inputrc, but it disappears in these libexec cases.
#
# MacOS's system ruby installation falls in this category, which means that running irb under the
# system ruby doesn't get vi mode, but this file should fix that. Note that irb under
# rbenv-installed rubies uses readline and ~/.inputrc, so it works in those cases.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# set vi mode
bind -v
